frame handling

when our element is a frame , we will get no such element exception
we get this issue when our locator is wrong or selenium is interacting fastly

when No such element exception occur:
first check for locator(check if locator is correct)
then for if page is loading slower(use sleep or wait)
and lastly for if frame is there(use frame switching)

A frame (or iframe) is like a webpage inside another webpage.
Selenium cannot directly interact with elements inside a frame unless you switch to it first.

If you try:driver.find_element(....) on an element inside a frame → ❌ NoSuchElementException.Because Selenium is still in the main page context

How to Handle Frames in Selenium:
1. Switch using index:
driver.switch_to.frame(0)
0 = first frame on page

2.Switch using name or id
driver.switch_to.frame("frameName")

3. Switch using WebElement (Most reliable )
frame = driver.find_element(By.XPATH, "//iframe[@id='frame1']")
driver.switch_to.frame(frame)

above we are moving from parent to child now we will switch from child to parent

1.Go from child → parent frame
driver.switch_to.parent_frame()
This moves one level up only

2. Go from any frame → main page (default content)
driver.switch_to.default_content()
This jumps directly to main page, skipping all parent levels


